{
  "name": "Kyralis",
  "type": "deity",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>It is said Kyralis was not <em>born</em> like the other gods, but <strong>emerged</strong> from the first ripple of death in the Life Stream — the moment the first living thing died. She made no sound then, and has spoken little since.</p><p>She holds dominion over the passing of all souls, guiding them back into the stream when their time comes, and ensuring the cycle of rebirth remains unbroken.</p><p>Legends say she can see <strong>all futures</strong>, but only ever speaks the ones that must come to pass.</p><p>She does not hate. She does not love. But she will never forgive the creation of the undead—a crime she sees as <em>warping the stream itself.</em></p>"
    },
